<item>
            <title>[LU-15014]  lu_ref_add() called in atomic context</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-15014</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;With the reintroduction of lu_ref to the native Linux client I turned on this functionality and started to test it. In my testing I saw the following errors:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;[ 2885.946815] Call Trace:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;[ 2885.951240]&#160; dump_stack+0x68/0x9b&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;[ 2885.956523]&#160; ___might_sleep+0x205/0x260&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;[ 2885.962245]&#160; lu_ref_add+0x25/0x40 &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;obdclass&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;[ 2885.968442]&#160; vvp_pgcache_current+0x101/0x1a0 &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;lustre&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;[ 2885.975370]&#160; seq_read+0x1ab/0x3c0&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;and&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;[ 7042.102529]&#160; dump_stack+0x68/0x9b&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;[ 7042.107328]&#160; ___might_sleep+0x205/0x260&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;[ 7042.112647]&#160; lu_ref_add+0x25/0x40 &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;obdclass&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;[ 7042.118385]&#160; mdc_lock_upcall+0x154/0x4d0 &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;mdc&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;[ 7042.124275]&#160; mdc_enqueue_send+0x508/0x580 &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;mdc&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;[ 7042.130225]&#160; ? mdc_lock_lvb_update+0x280/0x280&#160;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;mdc&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Its an easy fix that is missed since lu_ref is never tested on the OpenSFS branch.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
